81.1	Braveheart	Braveheart	Braveheart is a 1995 epic historical drama film directed by and starring Mel Gibson. The film was written for the screen and then novelized by Randall Wallace. Gibson portrays William Wallace, a 13th century Scottish warrior who gained recognition when he came to the forefront of the First War of Scottish Independence by opposing King Edward I of England (portrayed by Patrick McGoohan), who was also known by the nickname "Longshanks".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/55/Braveheart_imp.jpg/220px-Braveheart_imp.jpg
